              </span> <span style="text-transform: uppercase">September 04, 2025</span><br/></td></tr></tbody><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                House Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 70</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Assembly Member Arambula<br/><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i>(Coauthors: Assembly Members Addis, Aguiar-Curry, Alanis, Ávila Farías, Bains, Bauer-Kahan, Bennett, Berman, Boerner, Bonta, Bryan, Calderon, Caloza, Carrillo, Castillo, Chen, Connolly, Davies, DeMaio, Dixon, Elhawary, Ellis, Fong, Gabriel, Gallagher, Garcia, Gipson, Jeff Gonzalez, Mark González, Hadwick, Haney, Harabedian, Hart, Hoover, Irwin, Jackson, Kalra, Krell, Lackey, Lee, Lowenthal, Macedo, McKinnor, Muratsuchi, Nguyen, Ortega, Pacheco, Papan, Patel, Patterson, Pellerin, Petrie-Norris, Quirk-Silva, Ramos, Ransom, Rivas, Celeste Rodriguez, Michelle Rodriguez, Rogers, Blanca Rubio, Sanchez, Schiavo, Schultz, Solache, Soria, Stefani, Ta, Tangipa, Valencia, Wallis, Ward, Wicks, Wilson, and Zbur)<br/></i></font></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>August 29, 2025</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to Direct Support Professional Recognition Week. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">HR 70, as introduced, Arambula.
                          </span></div><div><span id="digesttext"/></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_81BC4AFD-68BE-46C0-BF10-3C1C501ADACF"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, September 7, 2025, to September 13, 2025, inclusive, is recognized nationwide as Direct Support Professional Recognition Week; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_747BD754-A4DA-4A4B-A4B1-F834BC1E4CE2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The Lanterman Developmental Disabilities Services Act (Lanterman Act) promises Californians with intellectual and developmental disabilities (IDD) the services and supports they need to pursue the lives of their own choosing; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E08DA3B7-B1DD-4A8D-BE03-BCED6A533A22"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California is the only state that has established this entitlement for services and supports for residents with IDD; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FE87AFEB-239F-44DD-A59E-0535A1443EF7"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The regional center system will serve more than 450,000 Californians with IDD and their families in the coming year; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_93E1346A-CD7A-4118-BF4A-1EF844B5F9E2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Direct support professionals provide services and supports to Californians with IDD and their families, becoming integral in their day-to-day lives; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F1CB318E-B7B8-4C56-8D6F-1B73CC293F6C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Every Californian with IDD deserves to participate as a valued member of their community; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_F30528C7-3166-4E62-90A1-B2540EC0AD11"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Direct support professionals provide essential support that empowers Californians with IDD to live safely in their homes and thrive in their communities; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_6922DE77-5DC8-4593-988C-F065A6E1A83B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The diverse direct support workforce, with women and people of color at the forefront, ensure culturally responsive services for Californians with IDD and their families across the state; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_A75724A2-F324-4503-9FF5-25E23D8D67FE"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Through their important work, direct support professionals promote independence and create opportunities that make inclusion a reality; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_409F4EF0-9F76-4D73-A220-62E5C5CE1FD0"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Assembly of the State of California, That the Assembly hereby declares the week of September 7, 2025, to September 13, 2025, inclusive, to be Direct Support Professional Recognition Week; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_654FC03E-72A6-48C4-AEE1-E1FB742D2D3D"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly, having recognized the rights of Californians with IDD through the Lanterman Act, finds that direct support professionals deliver on the state’s responsibility; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_DE5EB37E-E3FC-448B-8943-5E38509C4502"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly recognizes direct support professionals across the state for their commitment, diligence, and professionalism; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_228F920D-1C9C-4C04-8D24-A059A7365E69"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly honors direct support professionals for building a more inclusive and accessible California; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E2642D3C-C867-4841-9425-63952DBAC2AA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Assembly is committed to uplifting the direct support workforce and their valuable contributions to our state; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_E683A39C-A84A-4572-89F5-3241BC36E21A"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Chief Clerk of the Assembly transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span><font color="blue" class="blue_text"><i></i></font><div align="center"><span class="CorrectionsSeparator">___________________</span></div><br/><br/><span class="CorrectionsHeading"><span class="Correction">
